      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:574px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Uptake of free DNA fragments by a bacterial cell, leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4a578d172616927771884c86860c21\">heritable</span> changes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Growth Phase</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Log phase of bacterial growth.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Naturally Capable Bacteria</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Streptococcus pneumoniae <strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></li>\n<li>Haemophilus influenzae <strong>(Option D ruled out)</strong></li>\n<li>Neisseria gonorrhoeae <strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></li>\n<li>Bacillus</li>\n<li>Acinetobacter</li>\n<li>Pseudomonas</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Historical Significance</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-left:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-right:1px solid #1f1f1f; border-top:1px solid #1f1f1f; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Griffith's Experiment (1928): Demonstrated transformation using <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9562e26acc16927771995a2028dd05\">Streptococcus</span> pneumoniae in mice.</li>\n<li>Avery, MacLeod, and McCarty (1944): Identified DNA as the transforming principle.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
