    {
      "text": "Match the bacterial cell type with its correct description A) Hfr 1) A bacterial cell that lacks the F plasmid and can act only as a recipient in conjugation. B) F+ 2) A bacterial cell with an F plasmid that has excised from the chromosome and carries some chromosomal genes C) F\u207b 3) A bacterial cell that can act as a donor in conjugation, having the F plasmid incorporated into its chromosomal DNA D) F\u2019 4) A bacterial cell that has an F plasmid separate from its chromosomal DNA and can initiate conjugation",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "A - 1; B - 2; C - 3; D - 4",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "A - 2; B - 1; C - 4; D - 3",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "A - 4; B - 3; C - 1; D - 2",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "A - 3; B - 4; C - 1; D - 2",
          "correct": true
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "D. A - 3; B - 4; C - 1; D - 2",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/x5yLUXGqxhdzQ1SdH48H1744382350.png",
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/3OchyEDWdiJaUqWVjA6s1744382377.png"
